        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 9 at 6:14AM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 613 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Aliceville, moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Aliceville, Gordo, Union, Memphis, McMullen, Garden, Mantua, Jena,
Benevola, Johnston Lake, Gainesville Lake Campground, Snoddy,
Dillburg, Ralph, George Downer Airport, Kirk, Pleasant Ridge,
Pioneer, Cochrane, and Lewiston.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
